article_id:170,category_name:Events,title_name:Announcing the Raid Event New Year's Tidings: Fortune from Afar!,image_path:,message:<div>The New Year&#39;s Tidings: Fortune from Afar raid event will begin <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1546236000"></span>.</div><div><br></div><div>During this event, you can use Co-op Play to fight against the light-element raid boss!</div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/211c946c51dc2fc3251880ffd037af3c.png"></div><div>The new year is almost upon the Halidom! A group of people bringing blessings for the new year in samurai attire arrive from Hinomoto, a land to the east. But when a naginata-wielding young woman who was following that group shows up, the Halidom is thrown into an uproar! Will they all be able to safely ring in the new year?</div><div><br></div><div>About the Event:</div><div>The main new additions and changes in the New Year&#39;s Tidings: Fortune from Afar raid event are described below.</div><div><br></div><div>■ Additions:</div><div>・ You&#39;ll be able to enjoy special New Year&#39;s gimmicks, such as the raid boss dropping New Year&#39;s gifts, and kagami mochi appearing in maps.</div><div><br></div><div>■ Changes:</div><div>・ There&#39;s an even more extensive event story than the last raid event, Resplendent Refrain.</div><div>・ The appearance rate of the extra raid battle has been adjusted since the last raid event, Resplendent Refrain, to make it appear more frequently.</div><div><br></div><div>■ Notes:</div><div>1. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2, 2-1 (Normal) of the main story to participate.</div><div>2. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2, 2-1 (Normal) of the main story in order to play co-op.</div><div>3. The event schedule and content may change without warning.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for playing the Dragalia Lost game.</div>,start_time:1545890400,update_time1547104575